    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Effectiveness of Performance Management System</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Caroline.J</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">on Effectiveness of Performance<br />Management System</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5697</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Performance management is the process of creating a work environment or setting in which people are enabled to perform to the best of their abilities. Performance management is a whole work system that begins when a job is defined as needed. It ends when an employee leaves the organization.
While performance evaluation is limited in its scope and confined to reviewing the performance of employees, performance management is a much wider process. It is, infact, a total and integrated process comprising activities like goal setting, training, evaluation and rewarding of employees.
If the employee’s skills and knowledge are found to be insufficient, the required performance management process, training and development exercises are usually undertaken to achieve the required effectiveness.
In the absence of such a system, staff members are unclear as to the employer’s expectations regarding performance objectives and standards/targets, leading to low productivity, costly mistakes, stress, de-motivation, and conflict. Sound Performance Management Systems subscribe to the crucial Principle: “What gets measured gets done”.
The aim of this project ‘A Study On Effectiveness of the Performance Management System’ at AVA Cholayil Care Pvt, Ltd. is to assess the effectiveness of the existing performance management system adopted by the organisation and to find its impact on the employees. Also to identify the factors that play crucial role in making the PMS more effective and to improve my knowledge in this area.
This would help the organisation to an extent to get an idea about the effectiveness of the PM system and how far it benefits the employees and organisation.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10168">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10168</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
